data.name: txtNetworkTimeout.ToolTip
data.value:
Network timeout. Default 5 sec.
This value is set timeout for waiting reposnse from IP9212 device

data.name: txtCacheRead.ToolTip
data.value:
Cache timeout in seconds for reading switch values. Default 4 sec.
This value is used to cache "GetValue" result. Many times programs query all 16 switches one by one. So a little caching which will read all values in a row would be useful. Do not recomended to set too high values.

data.name: txtCacheConnect.ToolTip
data.value:
Cache timeout in seconds. Default 20 sec.
This value is used to cache "is connected" result. Some programs query driver up to every second is it still alive. With high network query intensivity the device can hang. So the driver is using "smart" caching technique (when it is safe to use cached value)

data.name: chkTrace.ToolTip
data.value: Driver will write ASCOM logs. Usefull for debugging problems

data.name: dataGridOutputSwitch.ToolTip
data.value: Aviosys IP9212 has different predefined statuses: OUT1 - OUT4: Normally closed relay (NС) OUT5 - OUT8: Normally opened relay (NO) This cannot be changed

data.name: ipaddr.ToolTip
data.value: IP addres of the device. Use "ipEdit.exe" to locate its IP addres

data.name: login.ToolTip
data.value: Login name. Factory default for the device is "admin"

data.name: pass.ToolTip
data.value: Device password. Factory default for the device is "12345678"
